    "52 for a two-photon classifier based on kernel methods.",
    "Following our photon-native approach, we design the ansatz of the variational algorithm directly using the beamsplitters and phase shifters on five modes of Ascella, in which we input three photons.",
    "We also implement partial pseudo photon-number resolution by exploiting four extra modes of the chip.",
    "We train the model using a see-saw optimization between the chip parameters and the output state parameters that define the measurement observable.",
    "Each iteration requires 112 experiments, one for each data point in the training set, and we gather 50,000 samples per run."
